    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>American architectural style of many public buildings 1933-1944, created in a relief program of the Great Depression and sponsored by the Public Works Administration (PWA) and the Works Progress Administration (WPA). Similar to Streamline Moderne, and may include elements of Beaux-Arts classicism and Art Deco,</Note_Text>
